 {r}‚Üê{bumpBuild}MakeServer batchFlag;F;targetPath;zipFilename;list;msg;success;parms;buff
‚çù Creates a new server.\\
‚çù Call this after `MakeClient` has been called; see there for details.
‚çù It can be called from a developer's session (‚çµ‚Üê0) or as part of an automated "Make" process with ‚çµ‚Üê1.\\
‚çù In case of a problem an error is thrown if ‚çµ=0 and ‚éïOFF 123 if ‚çµ=1.\\
‚çù You may call this independently from `MakeClient`.
‚çù `bumpBuild` must be a Boolean; 1 (the default) means that the build number will be bumped.
‚çù Other values result in an error or ‚éïOFF 123 respectively.
 r‚Üê‚ç¨
 bumpBuild‚Üê{0<‚éïNC ‚çµ:‚çé‚çµ ‚ãÑ 0}'bumpBuild'
 :If batchFlag
     ‚éïSHADOW'Assert'
